    "body": "You could run a cronjob every 7 minutes, I know its not exact, but it is good enough.\r\n\r\n```\r\ncrontab -e\r\n```\r\n\r\nAdd entry:\r\n```\r\n*/7 * * * * curl http://127.0.0.1:8080/db/backup\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn order not to waste space, perhaps create a script that removes the old files and adds a new file, the following script will keep the last 3 backups and remove everything else:\r\n```\r\n*/7 * * * * ~/.eth2/backup.sh\r\n```\r\n\r\n**~/.eth2/backup.sh**\r\n```\r\n#!/bin/bash\r\nls -t1 /home/ethereum/backups | tail -n +4 | xargs rm -r\r\ncurl http://127.0.0.1:8080/db/backup\r\nreturn 0\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
